WEBVTT

00:03.834 --> 00:07.041
(<i> rooster crows</i> )

00:08.291 --> 00:10.166
Brother John Bates,

00:10.208 --> 00:14.291
is that not the morning

00:10.208 --> 00:14.291
which breaks yonder?

00:14.333 --> 00:16.250
I think it be.

00:16.291 --> 00:18.875
But we have

00:16.291 --> 00:18.875
no great cause

00:18.917 --> 00:22.166
to desire

00:18.917 --> 00:22.166
the approach of day.

00:22.208 --> 00:23.667
(<i> rooster crows</i> )

00:25.333 --> 00:26.667
Who's there?!

00:26.709 --> 00:27.959
A friend.

00:28.000 --> 00:30.250
Under what Captain

00:28.000 --> 00:30.250
serve you?

00:30.291 --> 00:32.667
Under Sir Thomas Erpingham.

00:36.333 --> 00:39.041
I pray you

00:39.083 --> 00:42.083
what thinks he

00:39.083 --> 00:42.083
of our estate?

00:42.125 --> 00:43.834
Even as men wrecked upon a sand

00:43.875 --> 00:46.458
that look to be washed off

00:43.875 --> 00:46.458
at the next tide.

00:46.500 --> 00:48.583
He hath not told

00:46.500 --> 00:48.583
his thought to the king?

00:48.625 --> 00:51.875
No.

00:48.625 --> 00:51.875
Nor it is not meet he should.

00:51.917 --> 00:54.125
For though I speak it to you

00:54.166 --> 00:59.417
I think the king is...

00:54.166 --> 00:59.417
but a man, as I am.

00:59.458 --> 01:02.375
The violet

00:59.458 --> 01:02.375
smells to him

01:02.417 --> 01:04.208
as it doth to me.

01:04.250 --> 01:07.709
In his nakedness,

01:04.250 --> 01:07.709
he appears but a man.

01:07.750 --> 01:11.417
Therefore his fears,

01:07.750 --> 01:11.417
out of doubt

01:11.458 --> 01:14.917
be of the same

01:11.458 --> 01:14.917
relish as ours are.

01:14.959 --> 01:18.333
Yet, no man should possess him

01:14.959 --> 01:18.333
with any appearance of fear

01:18.375 --> 01:21.667
lest he, by showing it,

01:18.375 --> 01:21.667
should dishearten his army.

01:21.709 --> 01:23.166
He may show

01:21.709 --> 01:23.166
what outward courage he will

01:23.208 --> 01:25.792
but I believe,

01:23.208 --> 01:25.792
as cold a night as 'tis

01:25.834 --> 01:28.000
he could wish himself in Thames

01:25.834 --> 01:28.000
up to the neck.

01:28.041 --> 01:31.750
Methinks I could not

01:28.041 --> 01:31.750
die anyplace so contented

01:31.792 --> 01:34.542
as in the king's company.

01:34.583 --> 01:36.709
His cause being just

01:36.750 --> 01:38.333
and his quarrel honorable.

01:38.375 --> 01:39.959
That's more than we know.

01:40.000 --> 01:42.250
Or more than we

01:40.000 --> 01:42.250
should seek after.

01:42.291 --> 01:44.041
If his cause be wrong,

01:44.083 --> 01:47.250
our obedience to the king

01:44.083 --> 01:47.250
wipes the crime of it out of us.

01:47.291 --> 01:49.333
But if the cause be not good,

01:49.375 --> 01:52.417
the king, himself, have

01:49.375 --> 01:52.417
a heavy reckoning to make

01:52.458 --> 01:55.166
when all those legs and arms and

01:52.458 --> 01:55.166
heads chopped off in a battle

01:55.208 --> 01:58.417
shall join together

01:55.208 --> 01:58.417
at the latter day and cry all

01:58.458 --> 02:00.083
"We died at such a place."

02:00.125 --> 02:01.709
The king is not bound to answer

02:01.750 --> 02:03.792
the particular endings

02:01.750 --> 02:03.792
of his soldiers,

02:03.834 --> 02:05.000
the father of his son,

02:05.041 --> 02:06.750
nor the master

02:05.041 --> 02:06.750
of his servant.

02:06.792 --> 02:09.083
Splendid, Data, splendid.

02:09.125 --> 02:10.709
You're getting

02:09.125 --> 02:10.709
better and better.

02:10.750 --> 02:12.792
Freeze program.

02:16.625 --> 02:18.041
Thank you, sir.

02:18.083 --> 02:21.709
I plan to study

02:18.083 --> 02:21.709
the performances

02:18.083 --> 02:21.709
of Olivier,

02:21.750 --> 02:23.709
Branagh, Shapiro

02:21.750 --> 02:23.709
and Kullnark.

02:23.750 --> 02:24.625
Data...

02:24.667 --> 02:25.709
(<i> sighs</i> )

02:25.750 --> 02:27.375
You're here to learn

02:27.417 --> 02:29.500
about the human condition.

02:29.542 --> 02:31.834
And there is no better way

02:29.542 --> 02:31.834
of doing that

02:31.875 --> 02:34.709
than by embracing Shakespeare.

02:34.750 --> 02:37.709
But... you must discover it

02:34.750 --> 02:37.709
through your own performance,

02:37.750 --> 02:40.083
not by imitating others.

02:40.125 --> 02:41.709
Riker to Picard.

02:40.125 --> 02:41.709
Sorry to interrupt, sir.

02:41.750 --> 02:43.083
Go ahead, Number One.

02:43.125 --> 02:44.667
Sensors are picking up

02:44.709 --> 02:47.083
a unidentified craft

02:44.709 --> 02:47.083
in the Neutral Zone.

02:47.125 --> 02:49.417
It's heading toward

02:47.125 --> 02:49.417
Federation space.

02:49.458 --> 02:51.125
We're on our way.

02:49.458 --> 02:51.125
Picard out.

02:51.166 --> 02:55.417
We'll get to the rest of the act

02:51.166 --> 02:55.417
another time, Data.

02:55.458 --> 02:57.417
Computer, file program

02:55.458 --> 02:57.417
and clear.

03:00.333 --> 03:01.792
Captain, why should a king

03:01.834 --> 03:03.667
wish to pass

03:01.834 --> 03:03.667
as a commoner?

03:03.709 --> 03:04.750
If he is the leader,

03:04.792 --> 03:06.458
should he not

03:04.792 --> 03:06.458
be leading?

03:06.500 --> 03:08.083
Listen to what

03:06.500 --> 03:08.083
Shakespeare

03:08.125 --> 03:10.667
is telling you

03:08.125 --> 03:10.667
about the man, Data.

03:10.709 --> 03:14.166
A king who had true

03:10.709 --> 03:14.166
feeling for his soldiers

03:14.208 --> 03:16.625
would wish to share

03:14.208 --> 03:16.625
their fears with them

03:16.667 --> 03:18.625
on the eve of battle.

03:18.667 --> 03:20.542
Sir, will I be able

03:18.667 --> 03:20.542
to schedule

03:20.583 --> 03:23.291
a performance for the crew

03:20.583 --> 03:23.291
in the near future?

03:23.333 --> 03:26.208
Let's not rush

03:23.333 --> 03:26.208
it, shall we?

03:26.250 --> 03:27.625
Hmm.

03:35.125 --> 03:37.667
Outpost Sierra VI

03:35.125 --> 03:37.667
confirms our readings, sir.

03:37.709 --> 03:39.750
They identify it

03:37.709 --> 03:39.750
as a Romulan scoutship.

03:39.792 --> 03:41.625
Bearing: 270 mark 14.

03:41.667 --> 03:43.583
Scoutship.

03:43.625 --> 03:46.000
What would a scoutship be doing

03:43.625 --> 03:46.000
this far into the Neutral Zone?

03:46.041 --> 03:47.792
Captain, shall

03:46.041 --> 03:47.792
we transmit

03:47.834 --> 03:49.166
a warning to withdraw, sir?

03:49.208 --> 03:50.667
Open a hailing frequency.

03:50.709 --> 03:52.041
Aye, sir.

03:52.083 --> 03:54.667
Captain, the Romulan

03:52.083 --> 03:54.667
is hailing us.

03:54.709 --> 03:56.041
Visual.

03:56.083 --> 03:57.667
Not within

03:56.083 --> 03:57.667
range, yet.

03:57.709 --> 03:59.208
Open a channel.

03:59.250 --> 04:01.458
Federation ship,

03:59.250 --> 04:01.458
do you read?

04:01.500 --> 04:03.458
I require urgent assistance.

04:03.500 --> 04:06.625
This is Captain Jean-Luc Picard

04:03.500 --> 04:06.625
of the USS...

04:06.667 --> 04:09.041
Federation ship,

04:06.667 --> 04:09.041
please help me.

04:09.083 --> 04:10.417
Requesting asylum.

04:10.458 --> 04:11.667
Under pursuit.

04:11.709 --> 04:13.208
Pursuit?

04:13.250 --> 04:14.625
Visual range.

04:14.667 --> 04:16.041
On screen, Captain.

04:51.709 --> 04:55.875
<i>Space, the final frontier.</i>

04:55.917 --> 04:59.917
<i>These are the voyages</i>

04:55.917 --> 04:59.917
<i>of the Starship</i> Enterprise.

04:59.959 --> 05:01.792
<i>Its continuing mission--</i>

05:01.834 --> 05:05.792
<i>to explore</i>

05:01.834 --> 05:05.792
<i>strange new worlds</i>

05:05.834 --> 05:10.333
<i>to seek out new life</i>

05:05.834 --> 05:10.333
<i>and new civilizations</i>

05:10.375 --> 05:14.792
<i>to boldly go</i>

05:10.375 --> 05:14.792
<i>where no one has gone before.</i>

06:17.417 --> 06:18.667
Red Alert.

06:18.709 --> 06:20.083
Open a channel to the warship.

06:20.125 --> 06:21.166
Come to intercept course.

06:21.208 --> 06:22.458
Keep us out

06:21.208 --> 06:22.458
of the Neutral Zone.

06:22.500 --> 06:24.083
Channel is open.

06:24.125 --> 06:26.500
How long before they cross over

06:24.125 --> 06:26.500
into Federation territory?

06:26.542 --> 06:27.834
41 seconds, sir.

06:27.875 --> 06:28.834
Romulan warbird,

06:28.875 --> 06:30.333
this is Captain Jean-Luc Picard

06:30.375 --> 06:32.709
of the Federation vessel

06:30.375 --> 06:32.709
<i>Enterprise.</i>

06:32.750 --> 06:34.834
You have crossed

06:32.750 --> 06:34.834
into the Neutral Zone

06:34.875 --> 06:37.083
and are engaged

06:34.875 --> 06:37.083
in hostile action.

06:37.125 --> 06:39.500
Explain yourself

06:37.125 --> 06:39.500
and your intent.

06:39.542 --> 06:41.750
No reply, sir.

06:41.792 --> 06:43.166
Hail the scout.

06:43.208 --> 06:44.709
Responding.

06:44.750 --> 06:46.125
On screen.

06:46.166 --> 06:47.583
Federation craft...

06:47.625 --> 06:50.333
please, you must help me!

06:50.375 --> 06:52.417
We are moving to intercept.

06:52.458 --> 06:54.333
Maintain your course and power.

06:58.917 --> 07:01.208
The scoutship

06:58.917 --> 07:01.208
is severely damaged, sir.

07:01.250 --> 07:03.458
Engines inoperative,

07:01.250 --> 07:03.458
shields are down.

07:03.500 --> 07:04.875
Position?

07:04.917 --> 07:07.291
Coordinates 140 by 205, sir.

07:07.333 --> 07:08.667
Federation space.

07:08.709 --> 07:10.250
Right. Move to within

07:08.709 --> 07:10.250
five kilometers.

07:10.291 --> 07:13.625
Mr. La Forge,

07:10.291 --> 07:13.625
prepare to extend

07:13.667 --> 07:15.250
our shields

07:13.667 --> 07:15.250
around the Romulan scoutship.

07:15.291 --> 07:17.166
At that range, the shields

07:15.291 --> 07:17.166
won't be able to take

07:17.208 --> 07:18.417
much punishment, Captain.

07:18.458 --> 07:19.834
Five kilometers, sir.

07:19.875 --> 07:21.458
All stop.

07:21.500 --> 07:22.959
Extend shields.

07:23.000 --> 07:24.417
LA FORGE:

07:23.000 --> 07:24.417
Shields in place.

07:24.458 --> 07:26.709
We've got the scoutship,

07:24.458 --> 07:26.709
Captain.

07:36.583 --> 07:39.000
The weapons on

07:36.583 --> 07:39.000
the warbird are

07:36.583 --> 07:39.000
fully powered, sir.

07:39.041 --> 07:41.250
Lock phasers.

07:39.041 --> 07:41.250
Open a channel.

07:41.291 --> 07:42.417
Ready.

07:42.458 --> 07:43.750
Romulan vessel

07:43.792 --> 07:46.041
you are now

07:43.792 --> 07:46.041
in Federation territory.

07:46.083 --> 07:49.000
Unless you withdraw...

07:49.041 --> 07:51.375
No argument?

07:51.417 --> 07:54.917
Warbird has re-entered

07:51.417 --> 07:54.917
the Neutral Zone.

07:54.959 --> 07:56.875
Heading

07:54.959 --> 07:56.875
toward Romulan territory.

07:56.917 --> 07:59.959
Massive power failure

07:56.917 --> 07:59.959
to the scoutship, sir.

08:00.041 --> 08:01.417
All systems are

08:00.041 --> 08:01.417
going off-line

08:01.458 --> 08:02.709
including

08:01.458 --> 08:02.709
life-support.

08:02.750 --> 08:04.208
Transporter 2,

08:02.750 --> 08:04.208
prepare to beam

08:04.250 --> 08:06.750
the occupant of the scoutship

08:04.250 --> 08:06.750
directly aboard.

08:06.792 --> 08:07.750
Aye, sir.

08:07.792 --> 08:08.917
Mr. Worf.

08:08.959 --> 08:11.750
Mr. Data,

08:08.959 --> 08:11.750
lock onto the scoutship.

08:11.792 --> 08:13.750
Take it in tow.

08:16.709 --> 08:17.959
Energize.

08:32.750 --> 08:34.667
I must see your Captain

08:32.750 --> 08:34.667
immediately.

08:34.709 --> 08:36.291
We'll get you

08:34.709 --> 08:36.291
to Sick Bay.

08:36.333 --> 08:37.250
After that...

08:37.291 --> 08:38.709
This cannot wait!

08:38.750 --> 08:41.959
I have information

08:38.750 --> 08:41.959
vital to your survival.

08:45.750 --> 08:49.834
<i>Captain's Log,</i>

08:45.750 --> 08:49.834
<i>Stardate 43462.5.</i>

08:49.875 --> 08:53.041
<i>We have beamed aboard</i>

08:49.875 --> 08:53.041
<i>an apparent Romulan defector</i>

08:53.083 --> 08:56.333
<i>who claims to be a low-ranking</i>

08:53.083 --> 08:56.333
<i>logistics officer</i>

08:56.375 --> 09:00.166
<i>with extraordinary information</i>

08:56.375 --> 09:00.166
<i>about a secret offensive.</i>

09:00.208 --> 09:02.625
The humiliating defeat

09:00.208 --> 09:02.625
at the battle of Cheron

09:02.667 --> 09:04.208
has<i> not</i> been forgotten.

09:04.250 --> 09:07.375
The new leaders have vowed

09:04.250 --> 09:07.375
to disregard the treaty

09:07.417 --> 09:09.208
and claim the

09:07.417 --> 09:09.208
Neutral Zone.

09:09.250 --> 09:11.458
Nelvana III is just

09:09.250 --> 09:11.458
the first step.

09:11.500 --> 09:12.917
You're saying an entire base

09:12.959 --> 09:14.625
has already been

09:12.959 --> 09:14.625
established there?

09:14.667 --> 09:18.417
Within 48 hours,

09:14.667 --> 09:18.417
the reactor core

09:14.667 --> 09:18.417
will be on-line.

09:18.458 --> 09:21.959
So the Federation sensors

09:18.458 --> 09:21.959
that monitor the Neutral Zone

09:22.000 --> 09:23.333
just missed it.

09:23.375 --> 09:25.834
It would seem so.

09:25.875 --> 09:28.959
In two days

09:29.000 --> 09:32.417
a fleet of Romulan warbirds

09:32.458 --> 09:35.291
will be within

09:32.458 --> 09:35.291
striking distance

09:35.333 --> 09:37.166
of 15 Federation sectors.

09:37.208 --> 09:39.041
The Federation

09:37.208 --> 09:39.041
will not permit that.

09:39.083 --> 09:43.542
Then it<i> is</i> war that we're

09:39.083 --> 09:43.542
talking about, isn't it?

09:45.208 --> 09:50.291
Destroy the base now

09:45.208 --> 09:50.291
and the threat is over.

09:50.333 --> 09:54.125
Well, I'm sure you are fatigued

09:50.333 --> 09:54.125
by your ordeal

09:54.166 --> 09:56.000
and you require

09:54.166 --> 09:56.000
medical attention.

09:56.041 --> 09:57.458
Lieutenant Worf

09:57.500 --> 10:00.208
will you conduct Sublieutenant

09:57.500 --> 10:00.208
Setal to the Sick Bay?

10:00.250 --> 10:03.208
We will attend

10:00.250 --> 10:03.208
to your quarters.

10:03.250 --> 10:06.500
No doubt you will wish

10:03.250 --> 10:06.500
to question me further.

10:08.375 --> 10:09.834
No doubt.

10:22.542 --> 10:24.041
He tells a hell of a story.

10:24.083 --> 10:25.625
You don't

10:24.083 --> 10:25.625
believe it?

10:25.667 --> 10:28.208
Well, the Empire knows

10:25.667 --> 10:28.208
that we would never allow them

10:28.250 --> 10:30.041
to build a base

10:28.250 --> 10:30.041
within the Neutral Zone.

10:30.083 --> 10:33.458
Commander, that would not be

10:30.083 --> 10:33.458
an atypical Romulan ploy.

10:33.500 --> 10:35.291
In their long

10:33.500 --> 10:35.291
history of war

10:35.333 --> 10:37.417
the Romulans have

10:35.333 --> 10:37.417
rarely attacked first.

10:37.458 --> 10:40.250
They prefer to test

10:37.458 --> 10:40.250
their enemy's resolve.

10:40.291 --> 10:41.750
RIKER:

10:40.291 --> 10:41.750
I think he's a plant

10:41.792 --> 10:43.542
to draw us

10:41.792 --> 10:43.542
into the Neutral Zone.

10:43.583 --> 10:45.667
That way, we look like

10:43.583 --> 10:45.667
the aggressors.

10:45.709 --> 10:47.250
And the Romulans would have

10:47.291 --> 10:49.667
a legitimate excuse

10:47.291 --> 10:49.667
for responding in force.

10:49.709 --> 10:50.667
Exactly.

10:50.709 --> 10:51.834
DATA:

10:50.709 --> 10:51.834
That would also

10:51.875 --> 10:53.750
not be an atypical

10:51.875 --> 10:53.750
Romulan ploy, sir.

10:53.792 --> 10:57.625
It's always a game

10:53.792 --> 10:57.625
of chess with

10:53.792 --> 10:57.625
them, isn't it?

10:57.667 --> 10:59.625
Well, at least

10:57.667 --> 10:59.625
he's given us

10:59.667 --> 11:01.125
a chance to get a look

11:01.166 --> 11:03.333
at some Romulan

11:01.166 --> 11:03.333
technology close-up.

11:03.375 --> 11:06.417
Mr. La Forge, you will

11:03.375 --> 11:06.417
lead the away team

11:03.375 --> 11:06.417
over to the scout.

11:06.458 --> 11:08.709
Commander, you

11:06.458 --> 11:08.709
and Counselor Troi

11:08.750 --> 11:10.667
will conduct Setal's

11:08.750 --> 11:10.667
interrogation.

11:10.709 --> 11:13.083
Captain, permission to

11:10.709 --> 11:13.083
observe the interrogation.

11:13.125 --> 11:14.834
No, Mr. Data.

11:14.875 --> 11:17.333
I need you

11:14.875 --> 11:17.333
on the bridge with me.

11:14.875 --> 11:17.333
There is much to be done.

11:17.375 --> 11:20.709
We have less than 48 hours

11:17.375 --> 11:20.709
to prevent a war

11:20.750 --> 11:23.041
or, perhaps...

11:23.083 --> 11:25.291
to start one.

11:25.333 --> 11:28.208
This will depend

11:25.333 --> 11:28.208
on establishing the truth...

11:35.250 --> 11:37.542
I set

11:35.250 --> 11:37.542
the autodestruct sequencer

11:37.583 --> 11:39.542
before I left the ship.

11:39.583 --> 11:40.542
Why?

11:40.583 --> 11:42.083
Wouldn't you?

11:42.125 --> 11:45.500
To prevent your ship

11:42.125 --> 11:45.500
from being captured?

11:45.542 --> 11:47.291
Excuse me for being

11:45.542 --> 11:47.291
a little confused, Setal

11:47.333 --> 11:48.500
but I thought

11:47.333 --> 11:48.500
you were defecting.

11:48.542 --> 11:51.500
I am not a traitor.

11:51.542 --> 11:57.166
All you can see is

11:51.542 --> 11:57.166
the opportunity to exploit me.

11:57.208 --> 12:00.625
The Federation credo--

11:57.208 --> 12:00.625
exploitation!

12:00.667 --> 12:03.208
Oh, you couldn't get aboard

12:00.667 --> 12:03.208
my ship fast enough, hmm?

12:03.250 --> 12:06.291
Strip it down.

12:06.333 --> 12:10.542
"What secrets might it reveal

12:06.333 --> 12:10.542
that we can use?"

12:10.583 --> 12:13.125
You're shortsighted people.

12:13.166 --> 12:15.000
Can't you understand?

12:15.041 --> 12:16.875
I came to stop a war.

12:16.917 --> 12:20.750
If you could

12:16.917 --> 12:20.750
just hold still.

12:22.792 --> 12:24.208
With your metabolism

12:24.250 --> 12:27.250
this will heal

12:24.250 --> 12:27.250
in a few moments.

12:32.917 --> 12:35.333
Thank you, Doctor.

12:35.375 --> 12:36.625
How fortunate

12:36.667 --> 12:39.333
that you know something

12:36.667 --> 12:39.333
of Romulan medicine.

12:39.375 --> 12:41.875
Yes, I had a chance to gain

12:41.917 --> 12:43.917
some experience

12:41.917 --> 12:43.917
recently.

12:43.959 --> 12:45.125
Oh, yes.

12:45.166 --> 12:47.291
The incident at

12:45.166 --> 12:47.291
the Galorndon Core.

12:47.333 --> 12:49.000
The two officers.

