22:13.834 --> 22:16.208
I want this report

22:13.834 --> 22:16.208
with dispatch.

22:20.458 --> 22:21.667
I don't know, Data.

22:21.709 --> 22:23.375
My gut tells me

22:21.709 --> 22:23.375
we ought to be listening

22:23.417 --> 22:25.375
to what this guy's

22:23.417 --> 22:25.375
trying to tell us.

22:25.417 --> 22:26.583
Your "gut"?

22:26.625 --> 22:28.875
It's just a...

22:26.625 --> 22:28.875
a feeling, you know--

22:28.917 --> 22:30.542
an instinct, intuition.

22:30.583 --> 22:32.583
But those qualities

22:30.583 --> 22:32.583
would interfere

22:32.625 --> 22:34.750
with rational judgment,

22:32.625 --> 22:34.750
would they not?

22:34.792 --> 22:36.542
You're right,

22:34.792 --> 22:36.542
sometimes they do.

22:36.583 --> 22:40.041
Then why not rely strictly

22:36.583 --> 22:40.041
on the facts?

22:40.083 --> 22:43.041
Because you just can't rely

22:40.083 --> 22:43.041
on the plain and simple facts.

22:43.083 --> 22:44.750
Sometimes they lie.

22:46.667 --> 22:48.625
They can lead

22:46.667 --> 22:48.625
to the wrong conclusions,

22:48.667 --> 22:50.750
but they cannot lie.

22:50.792 --> 22:52.709
Yeah? Well, what

22:50.792 --> 22:52.709
do you think?

22:52.750 --> 22:54.583
Is he a defector or not?

22:54.625 --> 22:56.000
The facts to date would lead

22:56.041 --> 22:58.041
to the objective conclusion

22:56.041 --> 22:58.041
that he is not.

22:58.083 --> 22:59.583
Well... somehow I think

22:59.625 --> 23:01.625
we're going to catch the

22:59.625 --> 23:01.625
Romulans with their pants down

23:01.667 --> 23:04.834
on Nelvana III,

23:01.667 --> 23:04.834
just like he says.

23:08.417 --> 23:10.166
"With their pants...?"

23:10.208 --> 23:11.583
A metaphor.

23:11.625 --> 23:13.750
Catching them in the act.

23:13.792 --> 23:15.959
Because your gut

23:13.792 --> 23:15.959
tells you so.

23:16.000 --> 23:17.291
Exactly.

23:17.333 --> 23:20.208
But you can't always

23:17.333 --> 23:20.208
go with your gut, either.

23:20.250 --> 23:21.375
It's...

23:21.417 --> 23:23.875
Well, it's

23:21.417 --> 23:23.875
a combination, Data.

23:23.917 --> 23:25.959
All right, I'll put it to you

23:23.917 --> 23:25.959
this way.

23:26.000 --> 23:29.250
All these feelings that get

23:26.000 --> 23:29.250
in the way of human judgment,

23:29.291 --> 23:31.000
that confuse the hell out of us,

23:31.041 --> 23:33.333
that make us

23:31.041 --> 23:33.333
second-guess ourselves--

23:33.375 --> 23:34.875
well, we need them.

23:34.917 --> 23:36.375
We need them to...

23:36.417 --> 23:37.875
help us fill in

23:36.417 --> 23:37.875
the missing pieces

23:37.917 --> 23:41.250
because we almost never

23:37.917 --> 23:41.250
have all the facts.

23:43.000 --> 23:47.458
So a person fills in

23:43.000 --> 23:47.458
the missing pieces of the puzzle

23:47.500 --> 23:51.792
with his own personality,

23:47.500 --> 23:51.792
resulting in a conclusion

23:51.834 --> 23:55.166
based as much

23:51.834 --> 23:55.166
on instinct

23:51.834 --> 23:55.166
and intuition

23:55.208 --> 23:56.333
as on fact.

23:56.375 --> 23:57.917
Now you're getting it.

23:57.959 --> 23:59.166
Hmm.

24:01.250 --> 24:02.875
But what does one do

24:02.917 --> 24:06.333
if he has no instinct

24:02.917 --> 24:06.333
or intuition?

24:07.750 --> 24:10.417
Data, look at this.

24:10.458 --> 24:13.792
The facts just took

24:10.458 --> 24:13.792
a left turn.

24:13.834 --> 24:16.834
DATA:

24:13.834 --> 24:16.834
As the probe went into

24:13.834 --> 24:16.834
orbit around Nelvana III,

24:16.875 --> 24:19.917
it began picking up

24:16.875 --> 24:19.917
low-level subspace

24:16.875 --> 24:19.917
radio emissions.

24:19.959 --> 24:22.417
Could they be

24:19.959 --> 24:22.417
naturally occurring?

24:22.458 --> 24:24.500
No, sir, the patterns

24:22.458 --> 24:24.500
are clearly artificial.

24:24.542 --> 24:26.166
The signal was so faint,

24:26.208 --> 24:28.291
our ship's sensors

24:26.208 --> 24:28.291
couldn't read it

24:26.208 --> 24:28.291
from this distance.

24:28.333 --> 24:29.834
Can we decode it?

24:29.875 --> 24:31.125
We've tried.

24:31.166 --> 24:33.041
It's probably Romulan,

24:31.166 --> 24:33.041
but we can't be sure.

24:33.083 --> 24:35.458
We've also picked up

24:33.083 --> 24:35.458
ionization disturbances.

24:35.500 --> 24:38.750
Cloaked Romulan ships

24:35.500 --> 24:38.750
could produce that effect.

24:38.792 --> 24:42.000
What about

24:38.792 --> 24:42.000
the planet's surface?

24:42.041 --> 24:44.375
Reading nothing

24:42.041 --> 24:44.375
but barren rock.

24:44.417 --> 24:47.000
I don't know.

24:44.417 --> 24:47.000
They might be able to hide

24:44.417 --> 24:47.000
a base from our probe.

24:47.041 --> 24:48.834
Its capabilities

24:47.041 --> 24:48.834
are limited.

24:48.875 --> 24:51.041
The only way

24:48.875 --> 24:51.041
we'll know for sure

24:51.083 --> 24:54.208
is if we go down

24:51.083 --> 24:54.208
and take a look

24:51.083 --> 24:54.208
for ourselves.

24:54.250 --> 24:57.375
That'll be all, gentlemen.

25:17.083 --> 25:22.709
I take it, you

25:17.083 --> 25:22.709
have never seen

25:17.083 --> 25:22.709
a Romulan before.

25:22.750 --> 25:25.875
That would be

25:22.750 --> 25:25.875
an incorrect assumption.

25:25.917 --> 25:29.291
Then why do you invade

25:25.917 --> 25:29.291
my privacy?

25:29.333 --> 25:33.625
I was attempting to ascertain

25:29.333 --> 25:33.625
what my guts tell me about you.

25:39.917 --> 25:43.083
You're the android.

25:43.125 --> 25:46.625
I know a host

25:43.125 --> 25:46.625
of Romulan cyberneticists

25:46.667 --> 25:48.458
that would love to be

25:48.500 --> 25:50.041
this close to you.

25:50.083 --> 25:54.083
I do not find that concept

25:50.083 --> 25:54.083
particularly appealing.

25:54.125 --> 25:56.959
Nor should you.

26:01.875 --> 26:04.333
I am told

26:01.875 --> 26:04.333
by various crew members

26:04.375 --> 26:07.125
that this viewport is

26:04.375 --> 26:07.125
their favorite on the ship.

26:07.166 --> 26:09.166
Hmm.

26:09.208 --> 26:13.417
I thought it would bring me

26:09.208 --> 26:13.417
some comfort,

26:13.458 --> 26:16.333
but these are not my stars.

26:16.375 --> 26:19.917
Even the heavens

26:16.375 --> 26:19.917
are denied me here.

26:21.917 --> 26:25.458
Oh... synthetic swill.

26:27.458 --> 26:30.041
I don't suppose

26:27.458 --> 26:30.041
your food terminals

26:30.083 --> 26:33.834
would be capable

26:30.083 --> 26:33.834
of producing a Romulan ale?

26:33.875 --> 26:35.375
I am afraid that would require

26:35.417 --> 26:38.000
the molecular structure

26:35.417 --> 26:38.000
of the beverage in question.

26:38.041 --> 26:39.875
And, as you are no doubt aware

26:39.917 --> 26:42.667
our knowledge of your planet

26:39.917 --> 26:42.667
is quite limited.

26:42.709 --> 26:44.750
The loss is yours.

26:44.792 --> 26:50.291
For I have visited

26:44.792 --> 26:50.291
over a hundred different worlds

26:50.333 --> 26:56.041
and none possessed

26:50.333 --> 26:56.041
the awesome beauty of Romulus.

26:56.083 --> 26:57.750
Am I correct in assuming

26:57.792 --> 27:00.166
you regret your decision

26:57.792 --> 27:00.166
to come here?

27:00.208 --> 27:04.750
What I did had to be done,

27:04.792 --> 27:09.250
but... never again

27:09.291 --> 27:14.792
to see the firefalls

27:09.291 --> 27:14.792
at Gal Gath'thong

27:14.834 --> 27:17.750
and the spires of my home

27:17.792 --> 27:22.000
as they rise

27:17.792 --> 27:22.000
above the Apnex Sea at dawn.

27:22.041 --> 27:27.000
It's a bitter thing

27:22.041 --> 27:27.000
to be exiled from your own home.

27:27.041 --> 27:29.959
It does appear

27:27.041 --> 27:29.959
unlikely

27:30.000 --> 27:32.834
you will ever be allowed

27:30.000 --> 27:32.834
to return to your planet.

27:32.875 --> 27:37.959
The cold reaction

27:32.875 --> 27:37.959
of an android.

27:42.166 --> 27:45.834
But perhaps we can bring Romulus

27:42.166 --> 27:45.834
to you.

27:49.667 --> 27:51.917
COMPUTER:

27:49.667 --> 27:51.917
Program complete.

27:51.959 --> 27:53.875
Run program.

27:56.291 --> 27:57.875
After you.

28:14.917 --> 28:16.917
The Valley of Chula.

28:16.959 --> 28:19.417
I know it well.

28:19.458 --> 28:24.083
You are free to stay here

28:19.458 --> 28:24.083
as long as you wish.

28:26.458 --> 28:28.875
I no longer live here.

28:28.917 --> 28:30.917
Turn it off.

28:34.250 --> 28:36.208
Cancel program.

28:37.875 --> 28:39.959
This...

28:40.000 --> 28:44.291
this is my home now,

28:40.000 --> 28:44.291
my future.

28:44.333 --> 28:46.875
I have sacrificed everything.

28:46.917 --> 28:51.875
It must not be in vain.

28:51.917 --> 28:55.250
Arrange a meeting between

28:51.917 --> 28:55.250
myself and Captain Picard.

29:00.041 --> 29:04.709
Tell him Admiral Jarok

29:00.041 --> 29:04.709
wants to see him.

29:10.750 --> 29:12.709
Captain, we have confirmed

29:12.750 --> 29:15.709
that you are holding

29:12.750 --> 29:15.709
Admiral Alidar Jarok.

29:15.750 --> 29:17.834
He has been identified

29:15.750 --> 29:17.834
as the commander

29:17.875 --> 29:19.917
at the massacre

29:17.875 --> 29:19.917
of the Norkan outposts.

29:19.959 --> 29:23.667
The council strongly advises

29:19.959 --> 29:23.667
that you consider Jarok

29:23.709 --> 29:26.208
an unreliable source

29:23.709 --> 29:26.208
of information.

29:33.583 --> 29:35.458
Bring him in.

29:37.875 --> 29:40.583
Ensign, will you

29:37.875 --> 29:40.583
wait outside?

29:43.500 --> 29:46.000
Have a seat,

29:43.500 --> 29:46.000
Admiral Jarok.

29:46.041 --> 29:48.583
Captain, there is

29:46.041 --> 29:48.583
no more time.

29:48.625 --> 29:50.959
Admiral,

29:48.625 --> 29:50.959
have a seat.

29:56.333 --> 30:01.583
You see, I'm just not convinced

29:56.333 --> 30:01.583
that you are telling the truth.

30:01.625 --> 30:04.333
What must I do?

30:04.375 --> 30:07.250
You must convince me.

30:07.291 --> 30:11.709
If I had irrefutable evidence...

30:11.750 --> 30:14.625
but you did not bring

30:11.750 --> 30:14.625
irrefutable evidence.

30:14.667 --> 30:16.583
You brought no evidence at all.

30:16.625 --> 30:19.709
And now I hear you are not

30:16.625 --> 30:19.709
the man you claimed to be.

30:19.750 --> 30:21.041
Admiral...

30:21.083 --> 30:25.834
your credibility

30:21.083 --> 30:25.834
is stretched

30:21.083 --> 30:25.834
beyond belief.

30:25.875 --> 30:31.166
A Romulan defector is almost

30:25.875 --> 30:31.166
a contradiction in terms.

30:31.208 --> 30:34.250
But Admiral Jarok

30:31.208 --> 30:34.250
crossing the lines?

30:34.291 --> 30:38.000
I explained my motivations

30:34.291 --> 30:38.000
to your interrogators.

30:38.041 --> 30:41.834
Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes--

30:38.041 --> 30:41.834
peace in our galaxy.

30:41.875 --> 30:44.667
Except, Admiral,

30:41.875 --> 30:44.667
you are not a man of peace.

30:44.709 --> 30:48.125
Your military record,

30:44.709 --> 30:48.125
what we know of it, is clear.

30:48.166 --> 30:52.458
Which is precisely why I chose

30:48.166 --> 30:52.458
an alternate identity here.

30:52.500 --> 30:55.834
The massacres in the Norkan

30:52.500 --> 30:55.834
outposts, for example.

30:55.875 --> 31:00.250
What you call "massacres"

30:55.875 --> 31:00.250
were called

31:00.291 --> 31:05.500
the "Norkan campaigns"

31:00.291 --> 31:05.500
on my world, Captain.

31:05.542 --> 31:10.125
One world's butcher

31:05.542 --> 31:10.125
is another world's hero.

31:10.166 --> 31:12.959
Perhaps I am neither one.

31:16.166 --> 31:20.709
On what basis, Admiral,

31:16.166 --> 31:20.709
am I to decide?

31:20.750 --> 31:22.542
Hmm?

31:24.792 --> 31:26.750
Your good word?

31:26.792 --> 31:29.583
Are you willing

31:26.792 --> 31:29.583
to help us overpower

31:29.625 --> 31:33.125
the Romulan B-Type warbirds

31:29.625 --> 31:33.125
we may encounter?

31:33.166 --> 31:36.417
Are you prepared

31:33.166 --> 31:36.417
to help us detect them

31:36.458 --> 31:38.834
through their

31:36.458 --> 31:38.834
cloaking shields?

31:41.291 --> 31:45.583
Well, you see

31:41.291 --> 31:45.583
my problem, Admiral.

31:45.625 --> 31:48.500
You ask us for faith

31:48.542 --> 31:52.166
in circumstances which are

31:48.542 --> 31:52.166
hardly possible to believe

31:52.208 --> 31:55.291
compounded by lies

31:52.208 --> 31:55.291
and your refusal to tell us

31:55.333 --> 31:56.417
what you know.

31:56.458 --> 31:58.709
I cannot betray my people.

31:58.750 --> 32:00.834
You've already betrayed

31:58.750 --> 32:00.834
your people, Admiral.

32:00.875 --> 32:02.208
You've made your choices, sir.

32:02.250 --> 32:04.125
You're a traitor.

32:04.166 --> 32:06.709
Now, if the bitter taste of that

32:04.166 --> 32:06.709
is unpalatable to you,

32:06.750 --> 32:09.000
I am truly sorry.

32:09.041 --> 32:11.250
But I will not

32:09.041 --> 32:11.250
risk my crew

32:11.291 --> 32:15.583
because you think you can dance

32:11.291 --> 32:15.583
on the edge of the Neutral Zone.

32:15.625 --> 32:19.000
You've crossed

32:15.625 --> 32:19.000
over, Admiral.

32:19.041 --> 32:23.333
You make yourself comfortable

32:19.041 --> 32:23.333
with that.

32:25.417 --> 32:30.291
Do you... have any children,

32:25.417 --> 32:30.291
Captain Picard, a family?

32:30.333 --> 32:33.000
No.

32:33.041 --> 32:39.667
Oh. Then you have sacrificed

32:33.041 --> 32:39.667
too much for your career.

32:39.709 --> 32:42.792
Yes, this is all

32:39.709 --> 32:42.792
very interesting...

32:42.834 --> 32:45.709
There comes a time

32:42.834 --> 32:45.709
in a man's life

32:45.750 --> 32:47.291
that you cannot know

32:47.333 --> 32:51.250
when he looks down at the first

32:47.333 --> 32:51.250
smile of his baby girl

32:51.291 --> 32:56.500
and realizes he must change

32:51.291 --> 32:56.500
the world for her--

32:56.542 --> 32:59.417
for all children.

32:59.458 --> 33:02.625
It is for her that I am here.

33:02.667 --> 33:07.834
Not to destroy the Romulan

33:02.667 --> 33:07.834
Empire, but to save it.

33:07.875 --> 33:10.041
For months

33:10.083 --> 33:14.166
I tried desperately

33:10.083 --> 33:14.166
to persuade the High Command

33:14.208 --> 33:17.709
that another war

33:14.208 --> 33:17.709
would destroy the Empire.

33:17.750 --> 33:19.625
They got tired of my arguments.

33:19.667 --> 33:21.667
Finally, I was censured,

33:21.709 --> 33:23.959
sent off to command

33:21.709 --> 33:23.959
some distant sector.

33:24.000 --> 33:28.208
This was my only recourse.

33:29.875 --> 33:32.125
I...

33:32.166 --> 33:37.750
will never see

33:32.166 --> 33:37.750
my child smile again.

33:37.792 --> 33:40.625
She will grow up

33:37.792 --> 33:40.625
believing

33:40.667 --> 33:45.417
that her father is a traitor.

33:45.458 --> 33:48.625
But she will grow up...

33:48.667 --> 33:49.875
if you act, Picard,

33:49.917 --> 33:54.750
if we stop

33:49.917 --> 33:54.750
this war before it begins.

33:54.792 --> 33:58.917
I can't and I won't...

33:58.959 --> 34:03.750
unless I have

33:58.959 --> 34:03.750
unequivocal cooperation.

34:20.083 --> 34:26.625
Admiral Jarok has provided me

34:20.083 --> 34:26.625
with the locations, strengths

34:26.667 --> 34:30.208
and tactical plans

34:26.667 --> 34:30.208
of the Romulan fleet.

34:30.250 --> 34:32.750
Mr. La Forge, he is prepared

34:32.792 --> 34:36.625
to give you data

34:32.792 --> 34:36.625
regarding engines,

34:36.667 --> 34:38.834
weapons, and the

34:36.667 --> 34:38.834
cloaking systems

34:38.875 --> 34:41.166
of the warbird

34:38.875 --> 34:41.166
class starship.

34:41.208 --> 34:42.792
But I believe

34:42.834 --> 34:46.000
his experience as a field

34:42.834 --> 34:46.000
commander will be more valuable

34:46.041 --> 34:49.000
for its strategic sense

34:46.041 --> 34:49.000
than in the technical areas.

34:49.041 --> 34:50.917
Any edge will help, Captain.

34:50.959 --> 34:52.166
Don't depend on this.

34:52.208 --> 34:53.417
For all we know,

34:52.208 --> 34:53.417
he may be still lying,

34:53.458 --> 34:55.125
but we shall find that out

34:53.458 --> 34:55.125
soon enough.

34:55.166 --> 34:56.083
Number One,

34:56.125 --> 34:58.417
set course for Nelvana III.

35:04.333 --> 35:07.875
DATA:

35:04.333 --> 35:07.875
<i>Second Officer's Log,</i>

35:04.333 --> 35:07.875
<i>Stardate 43465.2.</i>

35:07.917 --> 35:09.750
<i>We have entered</i>

35:07.917 --> 35:09.750
<i>the Neutral Zone</i>

35:09.792 --> 35:12.625
<i>in direct violation</i>

35:09.792 --> 35:12.625
<i>of the Treaty of Algeron.</i>

35:12.667 --> 35:15.917
<i>Presuming Romulan warships</i>

35:12.667 --> 35:15.917
<i>are cloaked and monitoring us,</i>

35:15.959 --> 35:17.625
<i>we expect heavy resistance</i>

35:17.667 --> 35:19.583
<i>as we approach Nelvana III.</i>

35:19.625 --> 35:20.542
Tactical?

35:20.583 --> 35:21.792
Nothing on sensors.

35:21.834 --> 35:23.959
I don't like it.

35:24.000 --> 35:26.667
I would have expected

35:24.000 --> 35:26.667
a greeting party.

35:26.709 --> 35:29.333
You echo

35:26.709 --> 35:29.333
another noteworthy commander

35:29.375 --> 35:31.125
in similar circumstances,

35:29.375 --> 35:31.125
Number One.

35:31.166 --> 35:33.333
A countryman

35:31.166 --> 35:33.333
of yours--

35:33.375 --> 35:34.875
George Armstrong Custer

35:34.917 --> 35:38.625
when his Seventh Cavalry

35:34.917 --> 35:38.625
arrived at The Little Bighorn.

35:38.667 --> 35:40.291
May we have better luck.

35:40.333 --> 35:42.333
Approaching Nelvana system.

35:42.375 --> 35:44.542
Engage impulse engines.

35:49.458 --> 35:51.458
Nelvana III on screen.

35:57.834 --> 36:00.542
Still no signs of them

35:57.834 --> 36:00.542
on sensors.

36:00.583 --> 36:04.125
In a way, I'd rather be fighting

36:00.583 --> 36:04.125
my way through this.

36:04.166 --> 36:05.709
It's just too damned easy.

36:05.750 --> 36:08.166
Prepare to enter

36:05.750 --> 36:08.166
standard orbit.

36:14.375 --> 36:15.333
Data?

36:15.375 --> 36:17.500
Scanning

36:15.375 --> 36:17.500
the planet, sir.

36:17.542 --> 36:21.041
No life forms, no power sources,

36:17.542 --> 36:21.041
no weapons systems.

36:21.083 --> 36:23.041
No indication

36:21.083 --> 36:23.041
of a base at all?

36:23.083 --> 36:24.417
DATA:

36:23.083 --> 36:24.417
No, sir.

36:24.458 --> 36:27.125
The subspace signal

36:24.458 --> 36:27.125
the probe detected?

36:27.166 --> 36:28.291
The ionization

36:27.166 --> 36:28.291
disturbances?

36:28.333 --> 36:30.709
DATA:

36:28.333 --> 36:30.709
I am picking them up, sir

36:30.750 --> 36:32.834
but I cannot identify

36:30.750 --> 36:32.834
the source.

36:32.875 --> 36:36.291
They seem to be moving

36:32.875 --> 36:36.291
in an orbital path

36:36.333 --> 36:39.208
with an 800-kilometer apogee.

36:42.458 --> 36:45.041
Lieutenant Worf,

36:42.458 --> 36:45.041
bring the Admiral up here.

36:45.083 --> 36:46.375
Aye, sir.

36:50.000 --> 36:53.333
Maybe they abandoned the planet

36:50.000 --> 36:53.333
after he defected.

36:53.375 --> 36:55.375
There is no scarring

36:53.375 --> 36:55.375
on the planet surface

36:55.417 --> 36:58.291
that would denote heavy

36:55.417 --> 36:58.291
construction of any kind.

36:58.333 --> 37:01.166
A cloaking device of some sort

36:58.333 --> 37:01.166
to hide the entire base?

37:01.208 --> 37:03.667
A cloaking device

37:01.208 --> 37:03.667
operating on the surface

37:03.709 --> 37:06.375
would be given away

37:03.709 --> 37:06.375
by visible distortion effects.

37:12.375 --> 37:14.542
Perhaps you would care

37:12.375 --> 37:14.542
to explain

37:14.583 --> 37:16.333
why we are here, Admiral.

37:16.375 --> 37:19.875
There doesn't appear

37:16.375 --> 37:19.875
to be a base.

37:23.709 --> 37:25.041
I don't understand.

37:25.083 --> 37:27.709
PICARD:

37:25.083 --> 37:27.709
Nelvana III, Admiral!

37:25.083 --> 37:27.709
No base!

37:27.750 --> 37:28.875
No weapons!

37:28.917 --> 37:31.291
No sign of any life at all!

37:36.417 --> 37:41.125
I-I saw

37:36.417 --> 37:41.125
the tactical communiqués--

37:41.166 --> 37:45.375
the records,

37:41.166 --> 37:45.375
timetables for completion.

37:45.417 --> 37:49.333
An entire legion

37:45.417 --> 37:49.333
was assigned to this section.

37:49.375 --> 37:53.667
Is it possible they could have

37:49.375 --> 37:53.667
been feeding you disinformation?

37:57.291 --> 37:59.500
You said

37:57.291 --> 37:59.500
that you had been censured--

37:59.542 --> 38:01.333
reassigned four months ago.

38:01.375 --> 38:03.917
They knew

38:01.375 --> 38:03.917
of your dissatisfaction.

38:03.959 --> 38:08.041
Could all this have been

38:03.959 --> 38:08.041
to test your loyalty?

38:08.083 --> 38:11.333
No.

38:11.375 --> 38:13.750
No!

38:13.792 --> 38:15.750
It's impossible.

38:26.208 --> 38:28.750
They let you escape

38:28.792 --> 38:31.750
with an arsenal

38:28.792 --> 38:31.750
of worthless secrets.

38:31.792 --> 38:34.834
What other explanation

38:31.792 --> 38:34.834
is there?

38:34.875 --> 38:36.834
Permission to withdraw

38:34.875 --> 38:36.834
from the Neutral Zone.

38:36.875 --> 38:38.500
At your earliest convenience,

38:36.875 --> 38:38.500
Number One.

38:38.542 --> 38:40.834
Helm, bring her around

38:38.542 --> 38:40.834
180 degrees!

38:40.875 --> 38:43.417
Geordi,

38:40.875 --> 38:43.417
get us out of here!

38:43.458 --> 38:45.667
GEORDI:

38:43.458 --> 38:45.667
I hear you, Commander.

38:53.500 --> 38:55.083
Two Romulan warships

38:53.500 --> 38:55.083
uncloaking.

38:55.125 --> 38:57.291
Coordinates...

39:04.959 --> 39:06.208
Shields holding.

39:06.250 --> 39:07.667
Damage?

39:07.709 --> 39:09.208
La FORGE:

39:07.709 --> 39:09.208
Minor damage

39:07.709 --> 39:09.208
to the secondary hull.

39:09.250 --> 39:11.291
Power transfer fields

39:09.250 --> 39:11.291
may be pinched off.

39:11.333 --> 39:13.667
I'm working on it.

39:13.709 --> 39:15.000
Captain?

39:15.041 --> 39:17.083
Not yet, Mr. Worf.

39:17.125 --> 39:19.625
This is just a tap

39:17.125 --> 39:19.625
on the shoulder

39:19.667 --> 39:22.250
or we wouldn't be here

39:19.667 --> 39:22.250
talking about it.

39:22.291 --> 39:24.500
The Romulans

39:22.291 --> 39:24.500
are hailing us.

39:24.542 --> 39:25.959
On screen.

39:26.000 --> 39:27.792
TOMALAK:

39:26.000 --> 39:27.792
Captain Picard,

39:27.834 --> 39:31.250
I hardly expected

39:27.834 --> 39:31.250
to see you again so soon.

39:31.291 --> 39:33.834
It seems this time

39:31.291 --> 39:33.834
<i>you</i> are the one

39:33.875 --> 39:37.166
who has made an aggressive move

39:33.875 --> 39:37.166
across the Neutral Zone.

39:37.208 --> 39:40.291
Commander Tomalak,

39:37.208 --> 39:40.291
as I am sure you already know,

39:40.333 --> 39:42.333
we were responding

39:40.333 --> 39:42.333
to warnings

39:42.375 --> 39:45.041
of Romulan incursions

39:42.375 --> 39:45.041
at Nelvana III.

39:45.083 --> 39:50.250
But, Captain, as you can see,

39:45.083 --> 39:50.250
there is no incursion.

39:50.291 --> 39:52.542
And the matter

39:50.291 --> 39:52.542
of the unidentified

39:52.583 --> 39:56.333
subspace radio emissions

39:52.583 --> 39:56.333
and the ionization disturbances?

39:56.375 --> 40:00.417
Oh, you must mean

39:56.375 --> 40:00.417
our orbiting probe.

40:00.458 --> 40:06.458
We are studying Nelvana III

40:00.458 --> 40:06.458
for... archaeological research.

40:06.500 --> 40:09.291
With a cloaked satellite?

40:09.333 --> 40:12.667
Oh, really, Captain,

40:09.333 --> 40:12.667
would you have us believe

40:12.709 --> 40:14.583
this satellite is an excuse

40:14.625 --> 40:17.166
for your aggressive charge

40:14.625 --> 40:17.166
across the Neutral Zone?

40:17.208 --> 40:19.500
You can believe

40:17.208 --> 40:19.500
what you wish,

40:19.542 --> 40:21.417
and we will be on our way.

40:21.458 --> 40:24.291
Without even an apology,

40:21.458 --> 40:24.291
Captain?

40:24.333 --> 40:28.041
If an apology will do,

40:24.333 --> 40:28.041
then I offer it.

40:28.083 --> 40:29.208
I'm afraid it won't,

40:29.250 --> 40:31.875
so I will save you

40:29.250 --> 40:31.875
the humiliation.

40:31.917 --> 40:33.792
Get to it, Tomalak!

40:33.834 --> 40:37.417
You see, Picard,

40:33.834 --> 40:37.417
after we dissect your<i> Enterprise</i>

40:37.458 --> 40:40.417
for every precious bit

40:37.458 --> 40:40.417
of information,

40:40.458 --> 40:43.125
I intend to display

40:40.458 --> 40:43.125
its broken hull

40:43.166 --> 40:44.959
in the center

40:43.166 --> 40:44.959
of the Romulan capitol

40:45.000 --> 40:46.709
as a symbol of our victory.

40:46.750 --> 40:50.291
It will inspire our armies

40:46.750 --> 40:50.291
for generations to come

40:50.333 --> 40:52.834
and serve as a warning

40:50.333 --> 40:52.834
to any other traitor

40:52.875 --> 40:55.333
who would create ripples

40:52.875 --> 40:55.333
of disloyalty.

41:00.709 --> 41:05.583
All the communiqués,

41:00.709 --> 41:05.583
all the timetables,

41:05.625 --> 41:08.959
all the records--

41:05.625 --> 41:08.959
they were all fiction

41:09.000 --> 41:10.917
written

41:09.000 --> 41:10.917
for my benefit.

41:10.959 --> 41:12.500
A test...

41:12.542 --> 41:15.834
a test of my loyalty.

41:15.875 --> 41:19.917
And you used me

41:15.875 --> 41:19.917
to lure the<i> Enterprise</i>

41:19.959 --> 41:22.333
into the

41:19.959 --> 41:22.333
Neutral Zone.

41:22.375 --> 41:28.291
First, Captain, you will

41:22.375 --> 41:28.291
return the traitor, Jarok.

41:28.333 --> 41:32.041
Then you will surrender

41:28.333 --> 41:32.041
as prisoners of war.

41:32.083 --> 41:34.917
Do you seriously expect me

41:32.083 --> 41:34.917
to accept those terms?

41:34.959 --> 41:41.625
No, Captain Picard,

41:34.959 --> 41:41.625
I expect you won't.

41:41.667 --> 41:45.333
You have 30 seconds to decide.

41:45.375 --> 41:47.667
I do not require

41:45.375 --> 41:47.667
one, Tomalak.

41:47.709 --> 41:52.500
I urge you, Captain Picard--

41:47.709 --> 41:52.500
surrender.

41:52.542 --> 41:55.542
Consider the men and women

41:52.542 --> 41:55.542
you would lead

41:55.583 --> 41:57.959
into a lost cause.

42:01.375 --> 42:05.333
If the cause is just

42:01.375 --> 42:05.333
and honorable,

42:05.375 --> 42:07.917
they are prepared

42:05.375 --> 42:07.917
to give their lives.

42:07.959 --> 42:10.625
Are you prepared

42:07.959 --> 42:10.625
to die today, Tomalak?

42:10.667 --> 42:16.000
I expected more from you

42:10.667 --> 42:16.000
than an idle threat, Picard.

42:16.041 --> 42:19.083
Then you shall have it.

42:19.125 --> 42:20.625
Mr. Worf.

42:20.667 --> 42:23.583
Aye, sir.

42:31.458 --> 42:34.667
Klingon warships--

42:31.458 --> 42:34.667
armed and ready, sir.

42:37.166 --> 42:39.875
What shall it

42:37.166 --> 42:39.875
be, Tomalak?

42:39.917 --> 42:44.083
You will still not survive

42:39.917 --> 42:44.083
our assault.

42:44.125 --> 42:47.208
And you will not survive ours.

42:47.250 --> 42:49.291
Shall we die together?

42:52.250 --> 42:56.667
I look forward to our

42:52.250 --> 42:56.667
next meeting, Captain.

42:59.667 --> 43:03.125
Romulan disrupters

42:59.667 --> 43:03.125
are powering down, sir.

43:08.041 --> 43:11.709
Cancel Red Alert.

43:13.750 --> 43:15.417
Mr. Worf, will

43:13.750 --> 43:15.417
you extend

43:15.458 --> 43:17.667
the appreciation

43:15.458 --> 43:17.667
of the Federation

43:17.709 --> 43:20.583
and my personal gratitude

43:17.709 --> 43:20.583
to the Klingons.

43:20.625 --> 43:22.667
Aye, sir.

43:22.709 --> 43:28.000
Take us back,

43:22.709 --> 43:28.000
Number One.

43:28.041 --> 43:32.583
I did it for nothing.

43:32.625 --> 43:37.125
My home, my family...

43:37.166 --> 43:39.500
for nothing.

43:50.625 --> 43:52.625
He ingested

43:50.625 --> 43:52.625
a Felodesine chip.

43:52.667 --> 43:54.709
He must have

43:52.667 --> 43:54.709
brought it with him.

43:54.750 --> 43:58.709
I'm sorry, Captain,

43:54.750 --> 43:58.709
there was no antidote.

43:58.750 --> 44:03.542
A letter to his wife

43:58.750 --> 44:03.542
and daughter.

44:03.583 --> 44:07.250
Sir, he must have known

44:03.583 --> 44:07.250
it would be impossible

44:07.291 --> 44:10.959
for us to deliver it.

44:11.000 --> 44:13.041
Today, perhaps,

44:13.083 --> 44:14.959
but if there are others

44:15.000 --> 44:17.166
with the courage

44:15.000 --> 44:17.166
of Admiral Jarok,

44:17.208 --> 44:19.834
we may hope to see

44:17.208 --> 44:19.834
a day of peace

44:19.875 --> 44:25.166
when we<i> can</i>

44:19.875 --> 44:25.166
take his letter home.
